title: Drawing, "End Table", early 20th century
medium: Graphite on tracing paper, double ruled border in orange color pencil
markings: Small stamp in red ink at lower right: DONALD DESKEY/ 145 WEST 57TH STREET/ NEW YORK CITY
inscribed: Inscribed in graphite with dimensions; lower right corner in graphite: SCALE 1 1/2"-1'0"/6337 [circled]; lower left corner in graphite: 11; lower right corner in red color pencil: P
description: Perspective, plan, and elevation drawing for low wooden (?) side table. Rectangular top of table and right side; shelf below extends beyond width of top surface. Top of table and lower shelf connected by two curved pieces of wood.

tombstone.epitaph:
Drawing, "End Table", early 20th century.
early 20th century. Graphite on tracing paper, double ruled border in orange color pencil. Gift of Donald Deskey. 1988-101-1262.
